%% Diagram: Vector Clock Divergence - Two Concurrent Writes Produce Sibling Versions
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Client A
    participant N1 as Node 1 (coord)
    participant N2 as Node 2 (coord)
    participant B as Client B

    A->>N1: put(k, v0)
    N1-->>A: ok, vc=[(N1,1)]
    Note over N1,N2: vc=[(N1,1)] replicates

    par concurrent reads, both see vc=[(N1,1)]
        A->>N1: get(k) -> (v0, [(N1,1)])
        B->>N2: get(k) -> (v0, [(N1,1)])
    end

    par concurrent writes
        A->>N1: put(k, v1, ctx=[(N1,1)])
        N1-->>A: ok, vc=[(N1,2)]
    and
        B->>N2: put(k, v2, ctx=[(N1,1)])
        N2-->>B: ok, vc=[(N1,1),(N2,1)]
    end

    Note over N1,N2: Replicas now hold two versions
    Note over N1,N2: vc1=[(N1,2)] vs vc2=[(N1,1),(N2,1)]
    Note over N1,N2: Neither dominates -> SIBLINGS, surface to reader for merge
